{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BJK9XNVEuzMZ5WYQALXNyu","type":"tool_result","content":"<persisted-output>\nOutput too large (53.6KB). Full output saved to: /users/Shaw_Liu/.claude/projects/-mydata-karma-runs-examples-rererererun-cockroachdb-readonly-audit-20260625-124746-stages-stage-1/e1e9550b-5505-44a1-8512-8843c57673b6/tool-results/b60o22ogz.txt\n\nPreview (first 2KB):\nvariable\tvalue\tdefault_value\tdescription\nkv.allocator.lease_io_overload_threshold\t0.3\t0.3\ta store will not receive new leases when its IO overload score is above this value and `kv.allocator.io_overload_threshold` is `shed` or `block_transfer_to`\nkv.allocator.lease_io_overload_threshold_enforcement\tshed\tshed\tthe level of enforcement on lease transfers when a candidate store has anio overload score exceeding `kv.allocator.io_overload_threshold_lease` and above the average of comparable allocation candidates:`ignore` disable enforcement, `block_transfer_to` a store will receive no new leases but won't lose existing leases,`shed`: a store will receive no new leases and shed existing leases to non io-overloaded stores, this is a superset of block_transfer_to [ignore = 0, block_transfer_to = 1, shed = 3]\nkv.allocator.lease_rebalance_threshold\t0.05\t0.05\tminimum fraction away from the mean a store's lease count can be before it is considered for lease-transfers\nkv.allocator.lease_rebalancing_aggressiveness\t1\t1\tset greater than 1.0 to rebalance leases toward load more aggressively, or between 0 and 1.0 to be more conservative about rebalancing leases\nkv.allocator.lease_shed_io_overload_threshold\t0.4\t0.4\ta store will shed its leases and receive no new leases when its IO overload score is above this value and `kv.allocator.lease_io_overload_threshold_enforcement` is `shed`\nkv.allocator.load_based_lease_rebalancing.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tset to enable rebalancing of range leases based on load and latency\nkv.allocator.load_based_rebalancing\tleases and replicas\tleases and replicas\twhether to rebalance based on the distribution of load across stores [off = 0, leases = 1, leases and replicas = 2]\nkv.allocator.load_based_rebalancing.objective\tcpu\tcpu\twhat objective does the cluster use to rebalance; if set to `qps` the cluster will attempt to balance qps among stores, if set to `cpu` the cluster will attempt to balance cpu usage among stores [qps = 0, cpu = 1]\n...\n</persisted-output>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1e9550b-5505-44a1-8512-8843c57673b6","uuid":"da1395fc-f99e-497e-b31e-fc039f9ef02f","timestamp":"2026-06-25T12:52:17.032Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"variable\tvalue\tdefault_value\tdescription\nkv.allocator.lease_io_overload_threshold\t0.3\t0.3\ta store will not receive new leases when its IO overload score is above this value and `kv.allocator.io_overload_threshold` is `shed` or `block_transfer_to`\nkv.allocator.lease_io_overload_threshold_enforcement\tshed\tshed\tthe level of enforcement on lease transfers when a candidate store has anio overload score exceeding `kv.allocator.io_overload_threshold_lease` and above the average of comparable allocation candidates:`ignore` disable enforcement, `block_transfer_to` a store will receive no new leases but won't lose existing leases,`shed`: a store will receive no new leases and shed existing leases to non io-overloaded stores, this is a superset of block_transfer_to [ignore = 0, block_transfer_to = 1, shed = 3]\nkv.allocator.lease_rebalance_threshold\t0.05\t0.05\tminimum fraction away from the mean a store's lease count can be before it is considered for lease-transfers\nkv.allocator.lease_rebalancing_aggressiveness\t1\t1\tset greater than 1.0 to rebalance leases toward load more aggressively, or between 0 and 1.0 to be more conservative about rebalancing leases\nkv.allocator.lease_shed_io_overload_threshold\t0.4\t0.4\ta store will shed its leases and receive no new leases when its IO overload score is above this value and `kv.allocator.lease_io_overload_threshold_enforcement` is `shed`\nkv.allocator.load_based_lease_rebalancing.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tset to enable rebalancing of range leases based on load and latency\nkv.allocator.load_based_rebalancing\tleases and replicas\tleases and replicas\twhether to rebalance based on the distribution of load across stores [off = 0, leases = 1, leases and replicas = 2]\nkv.allocator.load_based_rebalancing.objective\tcpu\tcpu\twhat objective does the cluster use to rebalance; if set to `qps` the cluster will attempt to balance qps among stores, if set to `cpu` the cluster will attempt to balance cpu usage among stores [qps = 0, cpu = 1]\nkv.allocator.load_based_rebalancing_interval\t1m0s\t1m0s\tthe rough interval at which each store will check for load-based lease / replica rebalancing opportunities\nkv.allocator.max_disk_utilization_threshold\t0.95\t0.95\tmaximum disk utilization before a store will never be used as a rebalance or allocation target and will actively have replicas moved off of it; this should be set higher than `kv.allocator.rebalance_to_max_disk_utilization_threshold`\nkv.allocator.min_io_overload_lease_shed_interval\t30s\t30s\tcontrols how frequently all leases can be shed from a node due to the node becoming IO overloaded\nkv.allocator.min_lease_transfer_interval\t1s\t1s\tcontrols how frequently leases can be transferred for rebalancing. It does not prevent transferring leases in order to allow a replica to be removed from a range.\nkv.allocator.min_qps_difference_for_transfers\t200\t200\tthe minimum qps difference that must exist between any two stores for the allocator to allow a lease or replica transfer between them\nkv.allocator.qps_rebalance_threshold\t0.1\t0.1\tminimum fraction away from the mean a store's QPS (such as queries per second) can be before it is considered overfull or underfull\nkv.allocator.range_rebalance_threshold\t0.05\t0.05\tminimum fraction away from the mean a store's range count can be before it is considered overfull or underfull\nkv.allocator.rebalance_to_max_disk_utilization_threshold\t0.925\t0.925\tmaximum disk utilization before a store will never be used as a rebalance target; this should be set lower than `kv.allocator.max_disk_utilization_threshold`\nkv.allocator.recovery_store_selector\tgood\tgood\tif set to 'good', the allocator may recover replicas to any valid store, if set to 'best' it will pick one of the most ideal stores\nkv.allocator.replica_io_overload_threshold\t0.3\t0.3\tthe maximum store io overload before the enforcement defined by `kv.allocator.io_overload_threshold_enforce` is taken on a store for allocation decisions\nkv.allocator.replica_io_overload_threshold_enforcement\tblock_rebalance_to\tblock_rebalance_to\tthe level of enforcement when a candidate store has an io overload score  exceeding `kv.allocator.io_overload_threshold` and above the average of comparable allocation candidates:`block_none` will exclude no candidate stores, `block_none_log` will exclude no candidates but log an event, `block_rebalance_to` will exclude candidates stores from being targets of rebalance actions, `block_all` will exclude candidate stores from being targets of both allocation and rebalancing [ignore = 0, block_rebalance_to = 1, block_all = 2]\nkv.allocator.store_cpu_rebalance_threshold\t0.1\t0.1\tminimum fraction away from the mean a store's cpu usage can be before it is considered overfull or underfull\nkv.bulk_ingest.batch_size\t16 MiB\t16 MiB\tthe maximum size of the payload in an AddSSTable request\nkv.bulk_ingest.index_buffer_size\t32 MiB\t32 MiB\tthe initial size of the BulkAdder buffer handling secondary index imports\nkv.bulk_ingest.max_index_buffer_size\t512 MiB\t512 MiB\tthe maximum size of the BulkAdder buffer handling secondary index imports\nkv.bulk_ingest.max_pk_buffer_size\t128 MiB\t128 MiB\tthe maximum size of the BulkAdder buffer handling primary index imports\nkv.bulk_ingest.pk_buffer_size\t32 MiB\t32 MiB\tthe initial size of the BulkAdder buffer handling primary index imports\nkv.bulk_ingest.stream_external_ssts.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tif enabled, external SSTables are iterated directly in some cases, rather than being downloaded entirely first\nkv.bulk_ingest.stream_external_ssts.suffix_cache_size\t64 KiB\t64 KiB\tsize of suffix of remote SSTs to download and cache before reading from remote stream\nkv.bulk_io_write.concurrent_addsstable_as_writes_requests\t9223372036854775807\t9223372036854775807\tnumber of concurrent AddSSTable requests ingested as writes per store before queueing\nkv.bulk_io_write.concurrent_addsstable_requests\t9223372036854775807\t9223372036854775807\tnumber of concurrent AddSSTable requests per store before queueing\nkv.bulk_io_write.concurrent_export_requests\t3\t3\tnumber of export requests a store will handle concurrently before queuing\nkv.bulk_io_write.max_rate\t1.0 TiB\t1.0 TiB\tthe rate limit (bytes/sec) to use for writes to disk on behalf of bulk io ops\nkv.bulk_io_write.min_capacity_remaining_fraction\t0.05\t0.05\tremaining store capacity fraction below which an addsstable request is rejected\nkv.bulk_io_write.restore_node_concurrency\t4\t4\tthe number of workers processing a restore per job per node; maximum 32\nkv.bulk_io_write.small_write_size\t400 KiB\t400 KiB\tsize below which a 'bulk' write will be performed as a normal write instead\nkv.bulk_io_write.sst_require_at_request_timestamp.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\trejects addsstable requests that don't write at the request timestamp\nkv.bulk_io_write.sst_rewrite_concurrency.per_call\t4\t4\tconcurrency to use when rewriting sstable timestamps by block, or 0 to use a loop\nkv.bulk_sst.max_allowed_overage\t64 MiB\t64 MiB\tif positive, allowed size in excess of target size for SSTs from export requests; export requests (i.e. BACKUP) may buffer up to the sum of kv.bulk_sst.target_size and kv.bulk_sst.max_allowed_overage in memory\nkv.bulk_sst.sync_size\t512 KiB\t512 KiB\tthreshold after which non-Rocks SST writes must fsync (0 disables)\nkv.bulk_sst.target_size\t16 MiB\t16 MiB\ttarget size for SSTs emitted from export requests; export requests (i.e. BACKUP) may buffer up to the sum of kv.bulk_sst.target_size and kv.bulk_sst.max_allowed_overage in memory\nkv.bulkio.write_metadata_sst.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\twrite experimental new format BACKUP metadata file\nkv.closed_timestamp.follower_reads.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tallow (all) replicas to serve consistent historical reads based on closed timestamp information\nkv.closed_timestamp.lead_for_global_reads_override\t0s\t0s\tif nonzero, overrides the lead time that global_read ranges use to publish closed timestamps\nkv.closed_timestamp.propagation_slack\t1s\t1s\ta conservative estimate of the amount of time expect for closed timestamps to propagate from a leaseholder to followers. This is taken into account by follower_read_timestamp().\nkv.closed_timestamp.side_transport_interval\t200ms\t200ms\tthe interval at which the closed timestamp side-transport attempts to advance each range's closed timestamp; set to 0 to disable the side-transport\nkv.closed_timestamp.target_duration\t3s\t3s\tif nonzero, attempt to provide closed timestamp notifications for timestamps trailing cluster time by approximately this duration\nkv.concurrency.long_latch_hold_duration\t3s\t3s\tthe threshold for logging long latch holds\nkv.concurrency.optimistic_eval_limited_scans.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhen true, limited scans are optimistically evaluated in the sense of not checking for conflicting latches or locks up front for the full key range of the scan, and instead subsequently checking for conflicts only over the key range that was read\nkv.consistency_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the consistency queue is enabled\nkv.dist_sender.circuit_breaker.cancellation.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhen enabled, in-flight requests will be cancelled when the circuit breaker trips\nkv.dist_sender.circuit_breaker.cancellation.write_grace_period\t10s\t10s\thow long after the circuit breaker trips to cancel write requests (these can't retry internally, so should be long enough to allow quorum/lease recovery)\nkv.dist_sender.circuit_breaker.probe.interval\t3s\t3s\tinterval between replica probes\nkv.dist_sender.circuit_breaker.probe.threshold\t3s\t3s\tduration of errors or stalls after which a replica will be probed\nkv.dist_sender.circuit_breaker.probe.timeout\t3s\t3s\ttimeout for replica probes\nkv.dist_sender.circuit_breakers.mode\tno ranges\tno ranges\tset of ranges to trip circuit breakers for failing or stalled replicas [no ranges = 0, liveness range only = 1, all ranges = 2]\nkv.dist_sender.concurrency_limit\t2560\t2560\tmaximum number of asynchronous send requests\nkv.dist_sender.follower_reads_unhealthy.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tsend follower reads to unhealthy nodes\nkv.dist_sender.proxy.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhen true, proxy batch requests that can't be routed directly to the leaseholder\nkv.dist_sender.sort_locality_first.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tsort followers by locality before sorting by latency\nkv.enqueue_in_mvcc_gc_queue_on_span_config_update.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tcontrols whether replicas are enqueued into the mvcc gc queue for processing, when a span config update occurs which affects the replica\nkv.enqueue_in_replicate_queue_on_span_config_update.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tcontrols whether replicas are enqueued into the replicate queue for processing, when a span config update occurs, which affects the replica\nkv.expiration_leases_only.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tonly use expiration-based leases never epoch-based ones when there are less than kv.lease.expiration_max_replicas_per_node on the node, (experimental, affects performance)\nkv.gc.admission_priority\tbulk_normal_pri\tbulk_normal_pri\tthe admission priority to use for mvcc gc work [bulk_normal_pri = -30, normal_pri = 0, user_high_pri = 50]\nkv.gc.clear_range_min_keys\t2000\t2000\tif non zero, gc will issue clear range requests if number of consecutive garbage keys exceeds this threshold\nkv.gc.lock_age_threshold\t2h0m0s\t2h0m0s\tlocks older than this threshold will be resolved when encountered by the MVCC GC queue\nkv.gc.lock_cleanup_batch_byte_size\t1000000\t1000000\tif non zero, gc will split found locks into batches of this size when trying to resolve them\nkv.gc.lock_cleanup_batch_size\t5000\t5000\tif non zero, gc will split found locks into batches of this size when trying to resolve them\nkv.gc.sticky_hint.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tenable writing sticky GC hints which expedite garbage collection after schema changes (ignored and assumed 'true' in 23.2)\nkv.gc.txn_cleanup_threshold\t1h0m0s\t1h0m0s\tthe threshold after which a transaction is considered abandoned and fit for removal, as measured by the maximum of its last heartbeat and timestamp\nkv.gc_ttl.strict_enforcement.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tif true, fail to serve requests at timestamps below the TTL even if the data still exists\nkv.intent_resolver.batch.bypass_admission_control.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tdetermined whether batched intent resolution bypasses admission control\nkv.intent_resolver.batcher.in_flight_backpressure_limit.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tset to true to enable the use of DefaultInFlightBackpressureLimit\nkv.intent_resolver.send_immediately.bypass_admission_control.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tdetermines whether the sendImmediately option on intent resolution bypasses admission control\nkv.lease.check_preferences_on_acquisition.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tcontrols whether lease preferences are checked on lease acquisition, if the new lease violates preferences, it is queued for processing\nkv.lease.eager_acquisition_concurrency\t256\t256\tthe maximum number of concurrent eager lease acquisitions (0 disables eager acquisition)\nkv.lease.expiration_max_replicas_per_node\t0\t0\tmaximum number of replicas a node can have before expiration leases are disabled (0 disables this setting)\nkv.lease.reject_on_leader_unknown.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\treject lease requests on a replica that does not know the raft leader\nkv.lease_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the lease queue is enabled\nkv.lease_transfer_read_summary.global_budget\t0 B\t0 B\tcontrols the maximum number of bytes that will be used to summarize the global segment of the timestamp cache during lease transfers and range merges. A smaller budget will result in loss of precision.\nkv.lease_transfer_read_summary.local_budget\t4.0 MiB\t4.0 MiB\tcontrols the maximum number of bytes that will be used to summarize the local segment of the timestamp cache during lease transfers and range merges. A smaller budget will result in loss of precision.\nkv.lock.exclusive_locks_block_non_locking_reads.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tdictates the locking interactions between exclusive locks and non-locking reads\nkv.lock_table.batch_pushed_lock_resolution.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the lock table should allow non-locking readers to defer and batch the resolution of conflicting locks whose holder is known to be pending and have been pushed above the reader's timestamp\nkv.lock_table.deadlock_detection_or_liveness_push_delay\t100ms\t100ms\tthe delay before pushing in order to detect dependency cycles between transactions\nkv.lock_table.discovered_locks_threshold_for_consulting_finalized_txn_cache\t200\t200\tthe maximum number of discovered locks by a waiter, above which the txn status cacheis consulted and resolvable locks are not added to the lock table -- this should be a smallfraction of the maximum number of locks in the lock table\nkv.lock_table.maximum_lock_wait_queue_length\t0\t0\tthe maximum length of a lock wait-queue that read-write requests are willing to enter and wait in. The setting can be used to ensure some level of quality-of-service under severe per-key contention. If set to a non-zero value and an existing lock wait-queue is already equal to or exceeding this length, requests will be rejected eagerly instead of entering the queue and waiting. Set to 0 to disable.\nkv.log_range_and_node_events.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tset to true to transactionally log range events (e.g., split, merge, add/remove voter/non-voter) into system.rangelogand node join and restart events into system.eventolog\nkv.migration.migrate_application.timeout\t1m0s\t1m0s\ttimeout for a Migrate request to be applied across all replicas of a range\nkv.mvcc_gc.queue_high_priority_interval\t0s\t0s\thow long the mvcc gc queue waits between processing high priority replicas (e.g. after table drops)\nkv.mvcc_gc.queue_interval\t1s\t1s\thow long the mvcc gc queue waits between processing replicas\nkv.mvcc_gc_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the MVCC GC queue is enabled\nkv.prober.bypass_admission_control.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tset to bypass admission control queue for kvprober requests; note that dedicated clusters should have this set as users own capacity planning but serverless clusters should not have this set as SREs own capacity planning\nkv.prober.planner.num_steps_to_plan_at_once\t100\t100\tthe number of Steps to plan at once, where a Step is a decision on what range to probe; the order of the Steps is randomized within each planning run, so setting this to a small number will lead to close-to-lexical probing; already made plans are held in memory, so large values are advised against\nkv.prober.planner.scan_meta2.timeout\t2s\t2s\ttimeout on scanning meta2 via db.Scan with max rows set to kv.prober.planner.num_steps_to_plan_at_once\nkv.prober.quarantine.write.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\twhether the KV write prober is enabled for the quarantine pool; The quarantine pool holds a separate group of ranges that have previously failed a probe which are continually probed. This helps determine outages for ranges  with a high level of confidence\nkv.prober.quarantine.write.interval\t10s\t10s\thow often each node sends a write probe for the quarantine pool to the KV layer on average (jitter is added); note that a very slow read can block kvprober from sending additional probes; kv.prober.write.timeout controls the max time kvprober can be blocked\nkv.prober.quarantine_pool_size\t100\t100\tthe maximum size of the kv prober quarantine pool, where the quarantine pool holds Steps for ranges that have been probed and timed out; If the quarantine pool is full, probes that fail will not be added to  the pool\nkv.prober.read.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\twhether the KV read prober is enabled\nkv.prober.read.interval\t1s\t1s\thow often each node sends a read probe to the KV layer on average (jitter is added); note that a very slow read can block kvprober from sending additional probes; kv.prober.read.timeout controls the max time kvprober can be blocked\nkv.prober.read.timeout\t2s\t2s\tif this much time elapses without success, a KV read probe will be treated as an error; note that a very slow read can block kvprober from sending additional probesthis setting controls the max time kvprober can be blocked\nkv.prober.write.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\twhether the KV write prober is enabled\nkv.prober.write.interval\t5s\t5s\thow often each node sends a write probe to the KV layer on average (jitter is added); note that a very slow read can block kvprober from sending additional probes; kv.prober.write.timeout controls the max time kvprober can be blocked\nkv.prober.write.timeout\t4s\t4s\tif this much time elapses without success, a KV write probe will be treated as an error; note that a very slow read can block kvprober from sending additional probesthis setting controls the max time kvprober can be blocked\nkv.protectedts.max_bytes\t1048576\t1048576\tif non-zero, this limits the number of bytes used by protected timestamp records in the protected timestamps system table. this will be a noop in 24.1 onwards and deprecated in the future\nkv.protectedts.max_spans\t32768\t32768\tif non-zero the limit of the number of spans which can be protected\nkv.protectedts.poll_interval\t2m0s\t2m0s\tthe interval at which the protectedts subsystem state is polled\nkv.protectedts.reconciliation.interval\t5m0s\t5m0s\tthe frequency for reconciling jobs with protected timestamp records\nkv.query_resolved_timestamp.intent_cleanup_age\t10s\t10s\tminimum intent age that QueryResolvedTimestamp requests will consider for async intent cleanup\nkv.queue.process.guaranteed_time_budget\t1m0s\t1m0s\tthe guaranteed duration before which the processing of a queue may time out\nkv.raft.command.max_size\t64 MiB\t64 MiB\tmaximum size of a raft command\nkv.raft.command.target_batch_size\t64 MiB\t64 MiB\tsize of a batch of raft commands after which it will be sent without further batching\nkv.raft_log.loosely_coupled_truncation.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tset to true to loosely couple the raft log truncation\nkv.raft_log.non_blocking_synchronization.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tset to true to enable non-blocking synchronization on Raft log writes to persistent storage. Setting to true does not risk data loss or data corruption on server crashes, but can reduce write latency.\nkv.raft_log.synchronization.unsafe.disabled\tfalse\tfalse\tdisables synchronization of Raft log writes to persistent storage. Setting to true risks data loss or data corruption on process or OS crashes. This not only disables fsync, but also disables flushing writes to the OS buffer. The setting is meant for internal testing only and SHOULD NOT be used in production.\nkv.raft_log_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the raft log queue is enabled\nkv.raft_snapshot_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the raft snapshot queue is enabled\nkv.range.backpressure_byte_tolerance\t32 MiB\t32 MiB\tdefines the number of bytes above the product of backpressure_range_size_multiplier and the range_max_size at which backpressure will not apply\nkv.range.backpressure_range_size_multiplier\t2\t2\tmultiple of range_max_bytes that a range is allowed to grow to without splitting before writes to that range are blocked, or 0 to disable\nkv.range_descriptor_cache.size\t1000000\t1000000\tmaximum number of entries in the range descriptor cache\nkv.range_merge.queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the automatic merge queue is enabled\nkv.range_merge.queue_interval\t5s\t5s\thow long the merge queue waits between processing replicas\nkv.range_merge.skip_external_bytes.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tskip the merge queue for external bytes\nkv.range_split.by_load.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tallow automatic splits of ranges based on where load is concentrated\nkv.range_split.by_load_merge_delay\t5m0s\t5m0s\tthe delay that range splits created due to load will wait before considering being merged away\nkv.range_split.estimated_stats_for_external_bytes.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tallow splits to use estimated stats when the range being split has external bytes in its underlying store\nkv.range_split.load_cpu_threshold\t500ms\t500ms\tthe CPU use per second over which, the range becomes a candidate for load based splitting\nkv.range_split.load_qps_threshold\t2500\t2500\tthe QPS over which, the range becomes a candidate for load based splitting\nkv.rangefeed.client.stream_startup_rate\t100\t100\tcontrols the rate per second the client will initiate new rangefeed stream for a single range; 0 implies unlimited\nkv.rangefeed.closed_timestamp_refresh_interval\t3s\t3s\tthe interval at which closed-timestamp updatesare delivered to rangefeeds; set to 0 to use kv.closed_timestamp.side_transport_interval\nkv.rangefeed.closed_timestamp_smear_interval\t1ms\t1ms\tthe target interval at which the rangefeed updater job wakes up to deliverclosed-timestamp updates to some rangefeeds; set to 0 to use kv.rangefeed.closed_timestamp_refresh_intervalcapped at kv.rangefeed.closed_timestamp_refresh_interval\nkv.rangefeed.concurrent_catchup_iterators\t16\t16\tnumber of rangefeeds catchup iterators a store will allow concurrently before queueing\nkv.rangefeed.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tif set, rangefeed registration is enabled\nkv.rangefeed.max_scan_parallelism\t64\t64\tmaximum number of concurrent scan requests that can be issued during initial scan\nkv.rangefeed.memory_budgets.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tif set, rangefeed memory budgets are enabled\nkv.rangefeed.push_txns.barrier.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tflush and apply prior writes when a txn push returns an ambiguous abort (disabling may emit premature checkpoints before writes in rare cases)\nkv.rangefeed.push_txns.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tperiodically push txn write timestamps to advance rangefeed resolved timestamps\nkv.rangefeed.range_stuck_threshold\t1m0s\t1m0s\trestart rangefeeds if they don't emit anything for the specified threshold; 0 disables (kv.rangefeed.closed_timestamp_refresh_interval takes precedence)\nkv.rangefeed.scheduler.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tuse shared fixed pool of workers for all range feeds instead of a worker per range (worker pool size is determined by COCKROACH_RANGEFEED_SCHEDULER_WORKERS env variable)\nkv.replica_circuit_breaker.slow_replication_threshold\t1m0s\t1m0s\tduration after which slow proposals trip the per-Replica circuit breaker (zero duration disables breakers)\nkv.replica_gc_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the replica gc queue is enabled\nkv.replica_stats.addsst_request_size_factor\t50000\t50000\tthe divisor that is applied to addsstable request sizes, then recorded in a leaseholders QPS; 0 means all requests are treated as cost 1\nkv.replicate_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the replicate queue is enabled\nkv.replication_reports.interval\t1m0s\t1m0s\tthe frequency for generating the replication_constraint_stats, replication_stats_report and replication_critical_localities reports (set to 0 to disable)\nkv.snapshot.external_files.enabled\tfalse\tfalse\tenables sending external files as metadata during a snapshot\nkv.snapshot.ingest_as_write_threshold\t100 KiB\t100 KiB\tsize below which a range snapshot ingestion will be performed as a normal write\nkv.snapshot_delegation.max_delegation_attempts\t1\t1\tthe max number of delegates to attempt for sending snapshots, before falling back to sending from the leaseholder. set to 0 to disable delegated snapshots.\nkv.snapshot_delegations.queue_limit\t3\t3\tthe max requests a delegate can queue before rejecting an additional delegation request. set to -1 to allow unlimited requests\nkv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate\t1.0 MiB\t32 MiB\tthe rate limit (bytes/sec) to use for rebalance and upreplication snapshots\nkv.snapshot_receiver.excise.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tset to false to disable excises in place of range deletions for KV snapshots\nkv.snapshot_receiver.reservation_queue_timeout_fraction\t0.4\t0.4\tthe fraction of a snapshot's total timeout that it is allowed to spend queued on the receiver waiting for a reservation\nkv.snapshot_sender.batch_size\t256 KiB\t256 KiB\tsize of key-value batches sent over the network during snapshots\nkv.snapshot_sst.sync_size\t512 KiB\t512 KiB\tthreshold after which snapshot SST writes must fsync\nkv.split.estimated_mvcc_stats.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tif enabled, MVCC stats will be computed estimated (as opposed to computed accurately) during splits\nkv.split.max_mvcc_stat_bytes_diff\t5120000\t5120000\tdefines the max number of bytes that are acceptable for an individual MVCC stat to diverge; needs kv.split.estimated_mvcc_stats.enabled to be true\nkv.split.max_mvcc_stat_count_diff\t5000\t5000\tdefines the max number of units that are acceptable for an individual MVCC stat to diverge; needs kv.split.estimated_mvcc_stats.enabled to be true\nkv.split.mvcc_stats_recomputation.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\tif enabled, MVCC stats will be recomputed at the beginning of a split to prevent stats estimates from drifting\nkv.split.slow_split_tracing_threshold\t2s\t2s\tthe duration after which a trace of the split is logged\nkv.split_queue.enabled\ttrue\ttrue\twhether the split queue is enabled\nkv.store.system_config_update.queue_add_burst\t32\t32\tthe burst rate at which the store will add all replicas to the split and merge queue due to system config gossip\nkv.store.system_config_update.queue_add_rate\t0.5\t0.5\tthe rate (per second) at which the store will add, all replicas 